Togian Islands.title: Togian Islands
Togian Islands.byline: The Togian Islands are an archipelago in the Gulf of Tomini, Central Sulawesi in Indonesia.

Togdheer.title: Togdheer
Togdheer.byline: Named after the eponymous river which runs through the area, Togdheer is one of the administrative regions of the self-declared republic of Somaliland.
